The compass.png file is a licensed image from stock.adobe.com.

It has a transparent background, as indicated by the checkerboard, and
was downloaded in png format. Png supports transparent background, jpeg doesn't

The image was then resized, using the imagemagick convert program.
Resizing is peformed to reduce the size of the image file. The resizing does
not affect the size of the image displayed by the compass program.

Install imagemagick:
  sudo apt install imagemagick

Resize image:
  convert AdobeStock_1094425893.png -resize 1000x1000 compass.png

Imagemagick command examples:
  convert in.jpeg out.png
  convert in.jpeg -resize 50% out.png
  convert in.png -resize 50% out.png
  identify -format "%w x %h\n" out.png

